Let the areas of triangles \( \triangle ABC \) be \( S \), and note that the area of triangle \( ABC \) is given by \( S = \frac{1}{2} \left| \begin{array}{ccc}
A & B & C \\
\end{array} \right| \).

Since the circles are tangent from the outside, their centers \( A \), \( B \), and \( C \) form a triangle, so set up the matrix: 
\[
\begin{vmatrix}
A & B & C \\
\end{vmatrix}
= | \begin{array}{ccc}
3 & 2 & 1 \\
\end{array} |
\]

Compute the determinant: \( | \begin{array}{ccc}
3 & 2 & 1 \\
\end{array} | = 3 \times (2 \times 1 - 1 \times 3) - 2 \times (3 \times 1 - 1 \times 3) + 1 \times (3 \times 3 - 2 \times 2) \).
